-- HSBC, Standard Chartered Compete to Buy Majority Nedbank Stake, FT Reports
-- Alistair Holloway
-- 2010-07-24T11:32:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-24/hsbc-standard-chartered-compete-to-buy-majority-nedbank-stake-ft-reports.html

          
          
             HSBC Holdings Plc and Standard
Chartered Plc are in talks to buy Old Mutual’s 52 percent
holding in South Africa’s Nedbank, the  Financial Times  reported
in  Mark Kleinman ’s “In the Loop” column.  
 “Considerable” hurdles remain to any deal, Kleinman said,
citing people close to the transaction who weren’t named.  
